author: to know, be knowledgeable
glottocode: Pollex 06: Kite. :See, watch, know, notice, find; clever, bright, knowledgeable (Sta).

author: woman/female
glottocode: Female (I don't understand why this is treated as a suffix - MW)

author: to stab, pierce
glottocode: Pollex 06: Paatia. :Stab, thrust, inject; spear, javelin, lance (Sta).

author: to hit
glottocode: Kill pig or chicken (Bse); hit, beat

author: to split
glottocode: To be broken, as, for example, a coconut shell (Rsn)

author: dull, blunt
glottocode: Pollex 06: Muu/muu. :Not sharp, blunt (of husking stick, scissors, knives, etc) (Sta).

author: to swell
glottocode: Pollex 06: Puku. :Swelling, tumour; swell, become swollen (Sta).

author: egg
glottocode: Pollex 06: Hua. :Egg, fruit; to bear fruit.

author: short
glottocode: Low in status and short in elevation (Rmn)

author: this
glottocode: Pollex 06: Teeia. :This (this one with me, this one by me) (Sta).
